latestIgtvVideos.caption:

Click to watch the full video!

This is a typical booty workout for me at the moment when I’m in the gym, focusing on more compound exercises & not rushing each movement.

It’s all about the mind- muscle connection! It’s the ability to focus the tension you create during exercise on a specific muscle which is the difference between passively & actively moving the weight. It’s all well and good doing the technique but if you don’t have the above connection, then it won’t be effective.

I didn’t go too heavy for each movement here because my knees are weaker than usual so I’m trying to build the strength back gradually.

Like, share & SAVE this to give it a go 🙌🏻🥰🍑

Happy Sunday guys, hope you are all enjoying the bank holiday weekend 💗

True attractiveness isn’t about looks, it’s about your energy how you show up for yourself 🫶🏻

01- Active listening
Truly listening when others speak — making eye contact, not interrupting, and showing genuine interest makes people feel seen and valued.

02- Confidence (not arrogance)
Owning who you are, speaking with clarity, and being comfortable in your skin draws people in. Confidence is magnetic.

03- Emotional intelligence
Being aware of your own emotions and responding thoughtfully to others shows maturity and depth. It makes you feel safe and trustworthy to be around.

04- Kindness + compassion
Treating people with respect, generosity, and empathy is universally attractive. Kindness signals strength and self-worth.

05- Being passionate about something
People who care deeply about something (whether it’s a hobby, cause, or career) naturally radiate energy and purpose.

06- Being true to yourself
Authenticity is deeply attractive. When you own your quirks, values, and truth without pretending to be someone else, it inspires others to do the same.

07- Being present
Not being glued to your phone, showing up fully in conversations, and enjoying the moment makes others feel special in your presence.

08- Healthy boundaries
Knowing how to say no, protect your time, and honour your values signals self-respect — and invites others to respect you too.

09- Curiosity + open-mindedness
Genuine curiosity about the world and people around you makes conversations more engaging and meaningful.

10- Consistency + integrity
Doing what you say you’ll do, and being the same person across situations, builds trust and deep admiration.

Master these habits and watch your energy become magnetic. ✨

#habitsmakeresults #smallhabits #selfgrowthtips #glowuptips #energyiscontagious

This is your June reminder to soften your grip on urgency and trust that everything meant for you is already on its way. This is a month to choose peace over pressure, to move gently, and to remember that rushing isn’t required for blooming 💌

Here are 3 powerful prompts to start your June with:

01- Where in my life am I still holding on too tightly or rushing the outcome? What might open up for me if I softened into trust instead?

02- What does “peace over pressure” look and feel like in my day-to-day life? How can I choose that more often this month?

03- In what ways am I already blooming, even if the results aren’t fully visible yet? How can I honour and celebrate my quiet growth?

Stay open, grounded and let yourself receive with ease. 🫶🏻

#junevibes #growthmindsets #mindsetmotivations #shiftyourfocus #selfgrowthtips

New month, new energy ✨

Ad| I love the start of a new month because it’s a beautiful invitation to reset—mentally, emotionally, and energetically. It’s a chance to check in with your intentions, realign your energy, and move forward with grounded clarity.

3 ways I’m supporting my mental wellness this June:

01- Starting my mornings with intention and light 
I use my @lumie.lights Bodyclock Glow 150 to gently wake up and ease into the day and habit stack with my Lumie Dash while having breakfast. Light therapy can be part of your fresh start toolkit to naturally boost mood, focus, and energy. Plus it’s perfect for habit stacking! 

02- Journaling to connect with my mindset and goals
Taking a few minutes everyday to reflect or journal what’s on my mind helps me move through the month with clarity, intention and inner alignment.

03- Creating space for stillness 
Whether it’s a slow walk, deep breathing, or unplugged evenings—nourishing peace helps me show up with more presence.

Your new month doesn’t need a full reset—just a few grounded rituals that support your glow. Hope you have a beautiful June full of light and intention 🫶🏻

#newmonthvibes #amroutine #morningdiaries #lumielight

latestPosts.caption:
Your habits don’t just shape your day—they shape your mind. With consistency, you can rewire your subconscious to support growth, abundance, and calm. 🤍

These 3 simple practices have been transformational for me:

01- starting my day with positive affirmations 
Affirmations help to reprogram your mind by creating new neural pathways in your brain, cultivating new positive thought patterns, raising your vibration and attracting positive energy. I play my guided affirmation playlist as soon as I get up when doing my skincare because within the first 20 minutes of waking up, your subconscious is the most impressionable (making it the perfect time to plant empowering thoughts). 

02- gratitude journaling to attract abundance
Gratitude is one of the highest vibrational feelings you can tap into. Each morning, I write down 3–5 things I’m grateful for—big or small. This simple habit rewires your brain to notice the good, retraining your focus away from lack, stress, or comparison. Over time, this builds a mindset of abundance: you begin to expect good things, spot opportunities more easily, and navigate challenges with more grace. The more you focus on what you’re grateful for, the more you attract positive energy and opportunities into your life.

03- meditation to calm my mind 
One of the quickest ways to access and regulate the subconscious mind is through the breath.
A short daily practice of mindful breathing or meditation helps create a sense of inner safety—something the subconscious craves in order to release fear and reactivity. Even 5–10 minutes a day can be incredibly effective and brings you back to the present moment, where your true power lives. When you consistently return to calm and presence, you train your subconscious to trust that you’re safe to slow down, to choose, and to shift.

Hope these powerful habits help shift your mindset like they have for me! 🥰

Love C x 

#mindsettips #shiftyourmind #mindsetchanges
